                            <comment id="15098234" author="aaronlab" created="Thu, 14 Jan 2016 15:13:01 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;patch to fix issue, please accept asap.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="15098274" author="romseygeek" created="Thu, 14 Jan 2016 15:46:20 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;ack, thanks for picking this up Aaron.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="15098286" author="romseygeek" created="Thu, 14 Jan 2016 15:51:46 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Is there any reason to set maxDepth to 2?  It was Integer.MAX_VALUE before.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="15101819" author="aaronlab" created="Fri, 15 Jan 2016 14:19:07 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Alan, no particular reason other than I think it&apos;s silly to have the code check an unlimited number of directories/depth for the core.properties file.  I think 2 or 3 at most would be a reasonable limit, not sure why anyone would want to bury their solr cores anymore beyond that.  Feel free to change that particular setting to whatever you feel is right.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Thanks.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
