                            <comment id="15104994" author="romseygeek" created="Mon, 18 Jan 2016 09:23:23 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Thanks Aaron.  I set the search depth to 256, which seemed like a reasonable compromise.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Unfortunately I think this is probably a bit late for the 5.4.1 release (unless there&apos;s another respin), but if there&apos;s a 5.4.2 then I&apos;ll make sure it gets included.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="15134214" author="elyograg" created="Fri, 5 Feb 2016 14:01:38 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;We could bikeshed about the default depth limit forever. &lt;img class=&quot;emoticon&quot; src=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/images/icons/emoticons/smile.png&quot; height=&quot;16&quot; width=&quot;16&quot; align=&quot;absmiddle&quot; alt=&quot;&quot; border=&quot;0&quot;/&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;I think the default depth limit for software in Linux is 9.  256 seems rather high.  The number I thought of was 16.  Ultimately it&apos;s not up to me, as I&apos;m not the one working on it, but there&apos;s my two cents.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
